<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="557" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1007]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,730,755]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">Distribution.</emphasis>
From present records, 
<taxonomicName box="[635,752,730,755]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Helenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hesiformis">
<emphasis box="[635,752,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">hesiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be restricted to NE continental South 
<collectingCountry box="[1340,1436,730,755]" name="United States of America" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">America</collectingCountry>
reaching from Amazonas basin to French 
<collectingCountry box="[620,707,767,791]" name="Guyana" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">Guyana</collectingCountry>
and the nearby island of 
<collectingCountry box="[989,1088,766,791]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
. The record cited by Kormilev, 
<number box="[151,207,803,827]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" value="1962.0">1962</number>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[275,331,803,826]" name="Peru" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">Peru</collectingCountry>
: Upper Amazonas could belong to 
<taxonomicName box="[724,847,802,827]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Helenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wachteli" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[724,847,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">H.wachteli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[854,916,803,826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[854,916,803,826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="557" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[940,1014,802,827]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1654,1675]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,528,1616]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,519,1632]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 14. Distribution of Helenus species in Northern South and Central America." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255983/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="557">
